payload.queryText:
SELECT CAST(strftime('%s', 'now', '-1 minute') as INTEGER) as time, 4 as value 
WHERE time >= $__from / 1000 and time < $__to / 1000

targets.queryText:
WITH target_readable AS (
    SELECT key AS readable_target
    FROM vstring
    WHERE value = '$target'
),
source_readable AS (
    SELECT key AS readable_source
    FROM vstring
    WHERE value = '$source'
)
SELECT 
     vhash.*,  -- Select all columns from vhash
    '$target' AS target,
    '$source' AS source,  
    '$target' || '-' || '$source' AS combined_key  
FROM vhash
WHERE key = (
    SELECT readable_target || '-' || readable_source
    FROM target_readable, source_readable)
targets.rawQueryText:
WITH target_readable AS (
    SELECT key AS readable_target
    FROM vstring
    WHERE value = '$target'
),
source_readable AS (
    SELECT key AS readable_source
    FROM vstring
    WHERE value = '$source'
)
SELECT 
     vhash.*,  -- Select all columns from vhash
    '$target' AS target,
    '$source' AS source,  
    '$target' || '-' || '$source' AS combined_key  
FROM vhash
WHERE key = (
    SELECT readable_target || '-' || readable_source
    FROM target_readable, source_readable)

values: click anywhere on the map and copy GEOJSON button at the bottom left to use for the new records.
drag points and lines. Link new sources.
Snap line guides to nodes (blue) to attach to its path
for multisources every new source record target coordinates (geojson, or lon/lat) field should not be blank
for multisources every subsequent source record target coordinates (geojson, or lon/lat) field should not be blank
for multisource edges every subsequent record vertexA coordinates should not be blank
initial srcPath (path to source) can be a string or array
